The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Feb. 15: Passenger car sales saw an 8.17 per cent growth in January at 77,743 units against 71,867 units in the year-ago period, according to the Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers. Motorcycle sales jumped 22.8 per cent, fuelled by higher demand for Hero Honda and Bajaj Auto bikes. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 15: The civil aviation ministry today asked the finance ministry to continue with an earlier move exempting airlines and aircraft leasing firms from paying tax on lease hire charges. Both the state-run airlines and private ones like Air Sahara and Air Deccan have taken aircraft on lease. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 15: The government is examining allowing foreign direct investment (FDI) in the construction sector, commerce and industry minister Kamal Nath said today. ?We are examining it to spur development and generate employment in the rural sector,? he said. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 15: Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd (MTNL) has successfully offered voluntary retirement to over 1900 employees. MTNLs workforce has come down to over 52,000.

 Mumbai, Feb. 15: Patni Computer Systems will consider a proposal to raise capital through American depository receipts on February 19.




